CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. 20 reads: "Bishop Signs Register - Like all other guests, Bishop John J. Wright was required to sign the visitors' registry when he arrived as "open-house" guest at The House of Mary on Webster Ave. last week. Witnesses, left to right, are Sister M. Cyril, Mrs. Nellie Johnson, Mrs. Lelia Page, Nicole Page, Andrew Johnson, Mrs. Estella Smith, Billy James, Bishop Wright, Clarence Miller, Father Bassompierre, Edward Smith, Mrs. Lillian Dickerson, Clarence Holley, Mrs. Zora Bowman, J.D. Penny and Mrs. Mary L. White. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, including Andrew Johnson on left, women, boys, and girls, standing around Bishop John J. Wright in House of Mary, Webster Avenue
